Born Feb. 19, 1793, at Saint Clair Township, Allegheny Co., Pennsylvania, , to William Rigdon and Nancy Bryant. Ordained high priest in June 1831 by Lyman Wight; set apart as a counselor to President Joseph Smith on March 8, 1832, sustained as first counselor on March 18, 1833, at age 40; excommunicated Sept. 8,1844; diedJuly 14, 1876, at Friendship, Allegany Co., New York, at age 83.